South African Metals, Engineering Employers Reach Pay Deal With Main Union

-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 
2011-07-15T06:54:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-15/south-african-metals-engineering-employers-reach-pay-deal-with-main-union.html
The Steel and Engineering Industries
Federation of  South Africa  said it reached a pay agreement with
the National Union of Metalworkers of South Africa to end a pay
strike.  Details of the agreement will be announced on July 18, when
NUMSA’s members will return to work, SEIFSA, as the employer’s
organisation is known, said in a  statement  published on its
website today.  Talks with other labor unions in the industry will
continue, SEIFSA said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Durban, South Africa at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  